# Model 1: Outcome =  Drug + weight.gain_cat + BMI_cat + Age_cat + Sex

 Y.list = c("PCo1", "PCo2",  
            "Log2.A/P", "Log2.B/P", "Log2.F/B", 
            "Phylo.diver",  "InvSimpson", "Observed ASV", "Shannon")
model = list()
model.sum = list()
for (i in Y.list) {
  model[[i]] = lm(E.PCoA1[,i] ~   Drug + weight.gain_cat + BMI_cat + Age_cat + Sex, data = E.PCoA1)
  model.sum[[i]] =  summary(model[[i]])
  model.sum[[i]] = cbind(model.sum[[i]]$coefficients[,c("Estimate", "Std. Error", "Pr(>|t|)" ) ], model.sum[[i]]$adj.r.squared) %>% as.data.frame()
  colnames(model.sum[[i]])[4] = "adj.R-squared"
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], overall.p =  overall_p(model[[i]]))
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], AIC =  AICc(model[[i]])) %>% round(7)
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], dependent.var = i)
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], predictors = rownames(model.sum[[i]]))
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], var.P.adj = p.adjust(model.sum[[i]]$`Pr(>|t|)`, method = "fdr" ))
  model.sum[[i]] <- mutate(model.sum[[i]], star = cut(model.sum[[i]]$var.P.adj, breaks=c(-Inf, 0.001, 0.01, 0.05, 0.1, Inf), label=c("***", "**",  "*", "+", "")))
  model.sum[[i]]   = model.sum[[i]][-1,]
}
Model1 = do.call("rbind", model.sum) %>% mutate(No.model = "model1")
Model1 = Model1  %>% mutate(
                    New.Predictors = case_when(predictors == "DrugDTG" ~ "Drug: DTG",
                                               predictors == "DrugOther" ~ "Drug: Other",
                                               predictors == "BMI_catobese" ~ "BMI_cat: obese",
                                               predictors == "BMI_catoverweight" ~ "BMI_cat: overweight",
                                               predictors == "Age_catyoung" ~ "Age_cat: young",
                                               predictors == "SexM" ~ "Sex: M", 
                                               predictors == "weight.gain_catlose" ~ "Weight loss"))
row.names(Model1) = paste(Model1$predictors, Model1$dependent.var,"Model1", sep = "_")
knitr::kable(Model1, 
             row.names = F, align="c")  %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover", "condensed", "responsive")) %>%
  row_spec(which(Model1$var.P.adj < 0.05), bold = T, color = "Seagreen")

# Model 2: Outcome = Drug + weight.gain_cat + BMI_cat + Age_cat + Ethnicity
 Y.list = c("PCo1", "PCo2", "Log2.A/P", "Log2.B/P", "Log2.F/B", "Phylo.diver",  "InvSimpson", "Observed ASV", "Shannon")
model = list()
model.sum = list()
for (i in Y.list) {
  model[[i]] = lm(E.PCoA1[,i] ~   Drug + weight.gain_cat + BMI_cat + Age_cat + Ethnicity, data = E.PCoA1)
  model.sum[[i]] =  summary(model[[i]])
  model.sum[[i]] = cbind(model.sum[[i]]$coefficients[,c("Estimate", "Std. Error", "Pr(>|t|)" ) ], model.sum[[i]]$adj.r.squared) %>% as.data.frame()
  colnames(model.sum[[i]])[4] = "adj.R-squared"
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], overall.p =  overall_p(model[[i]]))
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], AIC =  AICc(model[[i]])) %>% round(7)
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], dependent.var = i)
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], predictors = rownames(model.sum[[i]]))
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], var.P.adj = p.adjust(model.sum[[i]]$`Pr(>|t|)`, method = "fdr" ))
  model.sum[[i]] <- mutate(model.sum[[i]], star = cut(model.sum[[i]]$var.P.adj, breaks=c(-Inf, 0.001, 0.01, 0.05, 0.1, Inf), label=c("***", "**",  "*", "+", "")))
  model.sum[[i]]   = model.sum[[i]][-1,]
}
Model2 = do.call("rbind", model.sum) %>% mutate(No.model = "model2")
Model2 = Model2  %>% mutate(
                    New.Predictors = case_when(predictors == "DrugDTG" ~ "Drug: DTG",
                                               predictors == "DrugOther" ~ "Drug: Other",
                                               predictors == "BMI_catobese" ~ "BMI_cat: obese",
                                               predictors == "BMI_catoverweight" ~ "BMI_cat: overweight",
                                               predictors == "Age_catyoung" ~ "Age_cat: young",
                                               predictors == "EthnicityCaucasian" ~ "Ethnicity: Caucasian",
                                               predictors == "weight.gain_catlose" ~ "Weight loss"))
row.names(Model2) = paste(Model2$predictors, Model2$dependent.var,"Model2", sep = "_")
knitr::kable(Model2, 
             row.names = F, align="c")  %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover", "condensed", "responsive")) %>%
  row_spec(which(Model2$var.P.adj < 0.05), bold = T, color = "Seagreen")

# Model 3: Outcome = BackBone + weight.gain_cat + BMI_cat + Age_cat + Sex
 Y.list = c("PCo1", "PCo2",  
            "Log2.A/P", "Log2.B/P", "Log2.F/B", 
            "Phylo.diver",  "InvSimpson", "Observed ASV", "Shannon")
model = list()
model.sum = list()
for (i in Y.list) {
  
  model[[i]] = lm(E.PCoA1[,i] ~   BackBone + weight.gain_cat + BMI_cat + Age_cat + Sex, data = E.PCoA1)
  
  model.sum[[i]] =  summary(model[[i]])
  model.sum[[i]] = cbind(model.sum[[i]]$coefficients[,c("Estimate", "Std. Error", "Pr(>|t|)" ) ], model.sum[[i]]$adj.r.squared) %>% as.data.frame()
  colnames(model.sum[[i]])[4] = "adj.R-squared"
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], overall.p =  overall_p(model[[i]]))
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], AIC =  AICc(model[[i]])) %>% round(7)
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], dependent.var = i)
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], predictors = rownames(model.sum[[i]]))
  model.sum[[i]] =  mutate(model.sum[[i]], var.P.adj = p.adjust(model.sum[[i]]$`Pr(>|t|)`, method = "fdr" ))
  model.sum[[i]] <- mutate(model.sum[[i]], star = cut(model.sum[[i]]$var.P.adj, breaks=c(-Inf, 0.001, 0.01, 0.05, 0.1, Inf), label=c("***", "**",  "*", "+", "")))
  model.sum[[i]]   = model.sum[[i]][-1,]
}
Model3 = do.call("rbind", model.sum) %>% mutate(No.model = "model3")
Model3 = Model3  %>% mutate(
                    New.Predictors = case_when(predictors == "BackBoneTAF" ~ "BackBone: TAF",
                                               predictors == "BMI_catobese" ~ "BMI_cat: obese",
                                               predictors == "BMI_catoverweight" ~ "BMI_cat: overweight",
                                               predictors == "Age_catyoung" ~ "Age_cat: young",
                                               predictors == "SexM" ~ "Sex: M", 
                                               predictors == "weight.gain_catlose" ~ "Weight loss"))
row.names(Model3) = paste(Model3$predictors, Model3$dependent.var,"Model3", sep = "_")

overall.sum$AIC_decision = ifelse(overall.sum$AIC - Reference.AIC == 0, NA, 
                           ifelse(overall.sum$AIC - Reference.AIC > 0, "Worse",    
                                                        "Better"))
overall.sum$dependent.var = factor(overall.sum$dependent.var,
                                      level = c("PCo1", "PCo2",

            Overall.p.value = mean(overall.p),
            No.mod          = "model3")
  sum.Model4 <- Model4 %>% group_by(dependent.var) %>% 
  summarise( adj.R_squared  = mean(`adj.R-squared`),
            AIC             = mean(AIC),
            Overall.p.value = mean(overall.p),
            No.mod          = "model4")
 overall.sum34  <-  rbind(sum.Model3, sum.Model4) %>% 
 mutate( Overall.star = cut(rbind(sum.Model3, sum.Model4)$Overall.p.value, breaks=c(-Inf, 0.000001, 0.00001, 0.001, 0.05, 0.1, Inf), label=c("***", "**",  "*", "++", "+","")))

                           ifelse(overall.sum34$AIC - Reference.AIC > 0, "Worse",   "Better"))

                                      level = c("PCo1", "PCo2",

                                      "Phylo.diver",  "InvSimpson", "Observed ASV", "Shannon"))
plot.data <- overall.sum
